13.6 Method References

1. Purpose Syntax & Usage: A method reference is described using :: (double colon) syntax.
                           For example, System.out::println refers to the println
                           method of the System.out object.

2. Functional Interfaces: They are used with functional interfaces.
3. Benefit: They make your code more readable and concise
4. Limitation: They can only be used for methods that fit the parameters and
               return type.


Syntax:
• Static Method References:
ClassName::staticMethodName

• Instance Method:
instance::instanceMethodName

• Instance Method Particular Class:
ClassName::methodName

• Constructor References:
ClassName::new


                  Lambda Expression               Method Reference

               s → s. toLowerCase()              String:: toLowerCase

               s -> s.toLowerCase ()             String:: toLowerCase

               (a, b) → a. compareTo (b)         For Integers it will be Integer:: compareTo and for
                                                 strings it is String:: compareTo

         (a, b) -> Person.compareByAge(a, b)     Person::compareByAge